WEBVTT

01:57.868 --> 02:01.371
<i>The deal between UBA
and Hyperion founder Paul Marks</i>

02:01.371 --> 02:03.999
<i>moved one step closer to completion
this week,</i>

02:03.999 --> 02:06.919
<i>with UBA's board of directors
formally recommending</i>

02:06.919 --> 02:11.340
<i>that shareholders vote on the sale at
the company's annual meeting next month.</i>

02:11.924 --> 02:15.636
<i>Critics are calling the deal reckless,
even dangerous.</i>

02:15.636 --> 02:19.556
<i>And as a former employee of UBA,
I have to agree.</i>

02:20.599 --> 02:23.894
<i>Should a billionaire
with an outsized aversion to the press</i>

02:23.894 --> 02:26.522
<i>be handed the keys
to a legacy media company</i>

02:26.522 --> 02:30.108
<i>at a time when truth matters
more than ever?</i>

02:33.070 --> 02:34.112
Everybody's jealous.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.824
So, there's been a lot of noise
about this deal.

02:37.824 --> 02:39.952
Big tech shouldn't be involved in media.

02:40.536 --> 02:43.747
Guys like me have too much influence,
too big a platform.

02:43.747 --> 02:44.665
We've heard it.

02:45.374 --> 02:48.085
Honestly, I'm probably the last person
that should be standing up here

02:48.085 --> 02:50.379
because I'm probably
the only person in this entire room

02:50.379 --> 02:51.755
that doesn't have a high school diploma.

02:51.755 --> 02:54.424
But, I want to be clear.

02:54.424 --> 02:58.136
I know what you guys do is essential,
and I'm here to support that.

02:58.720 --> 03:00.556
So, to that end,

03:00.556 --> 03:05.352
I am here to listen, be available,
and hopefully to start the conversation.

03:05.352 --> 03:08.730
So, if anybody has any questions,
fire away.

03:08.730 --> 03:12.651
Yeah. What's your take on the hack?
And do we know who's behind it?

03:12.651 --> 03:15.821
The operating theory right now is Russia.

03:15.821 --> 03:18.866
But I'm happy to have my forensics team
drill down into that

03:18.866 --> 03:20.492
and hopefully get to the bottom of it.

03:20.492 --> 03:25.163
Rest assured that from here on out,
your data will be secure.

03:25.163 --> 03:28.375
That kind of thing does not happen
at Hyperion.

03:28.375 --> 03:31.086
What about the people who work here
at <i>The Morning Show</i>?

03:31.670 --> 03:34.882
In this kind of a situation,
a lot of times people are laid off.

03:34.882 --> 03:40.220
Right. Well, my intention is to expand
the news division, not to gut it.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.973
It's probably a little too early
to get into the specifics of that.

03:42.973 --> 03:46.476
But once the ink is dry, we will review
the numbers.

03:49.396 --> 03:52.524
Yes, Alex. You don't have to
raise your hand.

03:53.483 --> 03:56.987
Hyperion is a multinational corporation,

03:56.987 --> 04:00.657
and you have close relationships
with governments, oligarchs--

04:00.657 --> 04:03.035
I'm not sure
I would characterize it that way, but...

04:03.035 --> 04:06.288
Well, how can we be sure
that news stories about Hyperion,

04:06.288 --> 04:08.999
or its associates, won't be spiked?

04:09.625 --> 04:10.792
Such as?

04:10.792 --> 04:14.796
Well, your company has contracts
with a number of law enforcement agencies.

04:14.796 --> 04:17.507
Alex, this is not a press conference.

04:17.507 --> 04:19.968
- We'll save that for after the deal.
- We're just asking questions.

04:19.968 --> 04:21.762
- It's okay.
- Just asking.

04:21.762 --> 04:23.180
Yeah. What? Was there a question?

04:23.180 --> 04:25.390
There are concerns that a police force
in Arizona

04:25.390 --> 04:30.312
was using your security software
to racially profile certain people.

04:31.730 --> 04:33.899
Norma Rae is coming in
a little hot this morning.

04:33.899 --> 04:37.653
Well, right. Well, I'm not exactly sure
how to respond to a rumor.

04:37.653 --> 04:40.739
I'm just saying it's a possibility
that there's a conflict of interest here.

04:40.739 --> 04:43.325
You know, on a number of issues.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.369
- Yeah.
- I've stated it before.

04:45.369 --> 04:49.581
I have absolutely no desire to determine
what is and what isn't newsworthy.

04:49.581 --> 04:52.751
That is Stella Bak's job,
and she is more than capable of doing it.

04:53.377 --> 04:54.753
Does that answer your question?

04:54.753 --> 04:55.879
Not entirely.

04:57.923 --> 05:02.135
Okay.
Well, why don't we sidebar that for later?

05:03.262 --> 05:05.180
Oh, God. Are you kidding me?

05:05.931 --> 05:10.894
Alex, if you could avoid accusing
our new partner

05:10.894 --> 05:14.064
of racially profiling the good people
of Arizona, that would be swell.

05:14.064 --> 05:17.609
We don't know what this guy does
or who he does it with.

05:17.609 --> 05:19.903
I personally just think
it's a reasonable thing to ask.

05:19.903 --> 05:24.241
Legal will be happy to walk you through
Paul's extensive business interests.

05:24.241 --> 05:26.285
But whatever personal thing you two have--

05:26.285 --> 05:28.829
I'm sorry. Personal?

05:30.247 --> 05:33.584
I saw your <i>Miss Saigon</i> helicopter arrival.
We all did.

05:33.584 --> 05:36.461
You mean when I single-handedly
brought him back to the table

05:36.461 --> 05:37.588
and saved your little deal?

05:37.588 --> 05:39.965
A deal you blew up in the first place?
No, no.

05:39.965 --> 05:42.843
You can't set a fire and then expect
a cookie when you put it out.

05:42.843 --> 05:44.761
Okay, I get it. All right? I get it.

05:44.761 --> 05:47.222
I pushed him out of the boat.
Brought him back into the boat.

05:47.222 --> 05:48.849
And it might've all been a little hasty.

05:48.849 --> 05:52.186
But now we have him back.
So we have to just do our due diligence.

05:54.188 --> 05:56.648
I want him on my show.
I wanna interview him.

05:59.818 --> 06:02.362
We're close to
the finish line on a negotiation

06:02.362 --> 06:05.532
- that has taken two fucking years...
- Two years.

06:05.532 --> 06:08.410
...and every Ivy League lawyer
from DC to Westchester,

06:08.410 --> 06:11.163
so can we skip you steering
that little boat of yours

06:11.163 --> 06:12.623
right onto the fucking rocks?

06:12.623 --> 06:17.252
Okay, Cory. I want this deal to go through
just as bad as you do.

06:17.252 --> 06:19.546
But there are a lot of skeptics out there.

06:19.546 --> 06:23.217
- I get it. No, I see.
- Great.

06:23.217 --> 06:26.595
You really do. You wanna be a partner.
You want that seat at the grown-up table.

06:26.595 --> 06:29.264
- But it's not your turn, Alex.
- Wow.

06:29.264 --> 06:34.102
I need you to cease and desist.
It's over. We vetted him.

06:34.686 --> 06:35.687
I haven't.

06:36.188 --> 06:37.481
Knock, knock.

06:38.732 --> 06:39.566
Is this a bad time?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.736
- Not at all. Please, come in.
- Yeah, I was just leaving. So...

06:42.736 --> 06:44.863
- Okay, thanks, Cory.
- Thank you, Alex.

06:47.324 --> 06:48.408
Good to see you again, Alex.

06:48.992 --> 06:49.993
Nice to see you.

06:50.577 --> 06:51.578
Okay.

06:52.996 --> 06:54.081
What was that all about?

06:54.081 --> 06:57.668
Well, welcome to the wonderful world
of talent management.

07:03.757 --> 07:04.633
Hi.

07:04.633 --> 07:06.969
- Hey. Hi. Sorry, we're early.
- Hey.

07:06.969 --> 07:09.179
- First time for you.
- Okay.

07:09.179 --> 07:12.474
- You must be Cheryl. Hi, hi.
- Sorry.

07:12.474 --> 07:14.434
- It's so great to finally meet you.
- Okay.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.271
- It's nice to meet you too.
- You're even prettier in person.

07:17.271 --> 07:18.522
Thank you.

07:19.523 --> 07:21.400
- And this must be Taylor.
- Yeah.

07:21.400 --> 07:23.485
- Taylor, hi. H-- Okay.
- Why don't you say hi?

07:24.319 --> 07:27.406
Hi. It's okay. Yeah?

07:27.406 --> 07:30.158
- Hi, I'm your auntie Bradley.
- Yeah.

07:31.159 --> 07:33.412
- Look at her.
- She kinda has Mom's face a little bit.

07:33.412 --> 07:35.497
- That freaks me out a little.
- Oh, yeah.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.584
- I mean... Dada.
- I'm a dad.

07:38.584 --> 07:39.877
- That's me. I did it.
- Wow.

07:39.877 --> 07:42.379
- Okay. Come on in, you guys.
- Thank you.

07:42.379 --> 07:43.589
Make yourselves at home.

07:44.089 --> 07:45.424
Wow.

07:45.424 --> 07:47.926
Cheryl, I don't know how to deal with

07:47.926 --> 07:49.469
- that pack-and-play thing.
- No, no.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.763
- Don't worry. They're impossible.
- Yeah.

07:53.932 --> 07:56.226
- That's how you do that.
- That's how you do that.

07:56.226 --> 07:58.645
I can't wait to see you do the news.

07:59.229 --> 08:00.522
Oh, right.

08:00.522 --> 08:04.026
Hey. I don't know if we're gonna have time
with the size of your to-do list, babe.

08:04.026 --> 08:05.235
Oh, really?

08:05.235 --> 08:07.279
- Maybe next time. Right, Brad?
- Yeah.

08:07.279 --> 08:08.739
But your bedroom's straight ahead...

08:08.739 --> 08:09.948
- Thank you.
- ...and I'll be right there.

08:09.948 --> 08:13.744
- Hey, Brad. Are you, like, a prepper now?
- I'm not gonna let you starve on my watch.

08:13.744 --> 08:16.413
All right,
I am gonna go help your lovely wife.

08:17.372 --> 08:19.708
I'm gonna send you some stuff
from your mom's house.

08:19.708 --> 08:24.546
- Her Hummels would look perfect in here.
- I don't really-- Hummels?

08:24.546 --> 08:27.799
Okay. Yeah, that would be nice.

08:27.799 --> 08:29.051
- Great to meet you.
- Indeed.

08:29.051 --> 08:30.761
- We'll see the next time.
- Yep.

08:32.095 --> 08:33.554
- Glen.
- Love that guy.

08:34.056 --> 08:36.933
- Stella Bak. There she is.
- What's up?

08:36.933 --> 08:39.269
- You're running late?
- Sorry. Yeah.

08:39.269 --> 08:44.566
Sports wants to build out programming
based on my Formula One team.

08:44.566 --> 08:46.401
- They had a lot of ideas.
- Yeah.

08:46.401 --> 08:48.362
They've been banned from staff retreats.

08:50.239 --> 08:53.200
Look at you running a major news division.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.911
Look at you, buying a major media company.

08:55.911 --> 08:58.247
I always knew
you'd end up at a place like this.

08:58.872 --> 09:02.167
I remember you telling me
that I wasn't cut out for tech.

09:02.751 --> 09:05.754
And you ignored me,
and you built your own start-up.

09:05.754 --> 09:06.964
Yeah.

09:06.964 --> 09:08.465
I've been keeping my eye on you.

09:08.465 --> 09:10.425
You're one of the reasons
I'm interested in this place.

09:12.177 --> 09:15.347
So, UBA News. What's on your wish list?

09:15.347 --> 09:16.598
Cutting right to it.

09:17.474 --> 09:19.685
- Well, I am running late.
- Yeah.

09:20.602 --> 09:23.230
I want more political coverage,
starting with midterms.

09:23.730 --> 09:27.359
Even Gen Z are watching network TV
when democracy is a cliff-hanger.

09:27.359 --> 09:28.277
Okay.

09:28.277 --> 09:30.696
And we're missing huge market shares
in digital.

09:30.696 --> 09:32.906
UBA could piggyback on your search engine

09:32.906 --> 09:36.660
and create a hybrid site with curated
headlines based on search histories.

09:36.660 --> 09:41.039
So you need resources to go
on the offensive using my technology.

09:43.709 --> 09:44.960
Why are you here?

09:46.670 --> 09:50.132
And don't tell me
it's to save the fourth estate.

09:54.303 --> 09:57.222
This place has been treading water
since Cory took over. Don't you think?

09:57.222 --> 09:58.891
We've had our share of challenges.

09:59.933 --> 10:01.185
Why are you covering for him?

10:03.437 --> 10:05.647
Paul. It's time.

10:06.732 --> 10:09.318
- It's time. Okay.
- Amanda.

10:09.318 --> 10:10.444
Stella.

10:10.444 --> 10:14.156
Great seeing you. We'll talk again.
Let's get a drink.

10:17.659 --> 10:19.203
What is next?

10:33.383 --> 10:34.635
This view!

10:36.678 --> 10:39.014
Wow.

10:40.265 --> 10:41.850
They don't call it the "Summit"
for nothing.

10:44.645 --> 10:47.314
The Empire State Building looks gorgeous.

10:48.190 --> 10:50.484
All I can think of is
<i>Sleepless in Seattle</i>.

10:50.484 --> 10:53.028
Yeah. Which I have now seen,
like, 20 times.

10:53.612 --> 10:55.948
- Really? I've never seen it. Is it good?
- Yeah.

10:55.948 --> 10:57.074
- You would love it.
- Yes.

10:57.074 --> 10:58.367
- You would absolute--
- Really?

10:58.367 --> 10:59.535
No, you would not love it.

11:01.745 --> 11:03.956
Uh-oh.

11:05.541 --> 11:08.585
- It's all the excitement.
- I think she's hungry, babe.

11:09.419 --> 11:10.796
Just give us a minute.

11:14.132 --> 11:17.094
It's okay, baby. Mama's got you.

11:18.136 --> 11:19.680
- I love her.
- Yeah?

11:19.680 --> 11:22.224
Oh, my gosh. Yes, she's amazing.

11:23.225 --> 11:24.393
Don't mess it up.

11:27.437 --> 11:30.732
Yeah. I'll try not to mess it up.

11:32.359 --> 11:35.779
Hey, I didn't mean it like that.
I'm proud of you.

11:35.779 --> 11:37.447
Hey, can I tell you something?

11:38.115 --> 11:38.991
Yeah.

11:40.576 --> 11:42.995
I'm turning myself in
for what I done at the Capitol.

11:44.538 --> 11:45.539
What?

11:46.790 --> 11:48.000
Two days from now,

11:48.584 --> 11:50.711
I'm gonna send Cheryl and the baby home,

11:50.711 --> 11:52.629
and I'm going into the FBI field office.

11:52.629 --> 11:54.423
She doesn't know anything about it yet,

11:54.423 --> 11:57.092
so I'd appreciate it
if you didn't say anything.

11:59.970 --> 12:01.847
Oh, my God, Hal.

12:05.350 --> 12:08.812
You don't need me to tell you
how stupid that is, do you?

12:10.814 --> 12:12.774
They are going to find me.

12:13.358 --> 12:15.194
Are you cra--
They're going through the footage.

12:15.194 --> 12:17.487
- They're pulling in everybody.
- Oh, my God.

12:17.988 --> 12:21.533
But they go easier on you
if you turn yourself in.

12:21.533 --> 12:23.160
Oh, my God.

12:23.160 --> 12:27.623
I do not need the FBI kicking my door in,
pointing a gun--

12:27.623 --> 12:29.750
No, Hal. Just no.

12:31.585 --> 12:33.962
Brad, I'll keep you out of it.

12:33.962 --> 12:36.173
How are you gonna keep me out of it?

12:37.132 --> 12:39.718
Five minutes after you confess to the FBI,

12:39.718 --> 12:42.971
they are gonna charge me
with destroying evidence

12:42.971 --> 12:45.224
and making a false statement.

12:45.224 --> 12:47.226
Both of those are felonies, Hal.

12:47.226 --> 12:49.269
No, I'm sorry. You can't do that.

12:49.269 --> 12:53.774
We have to put this behind us.
This is already behind us.

12:54.358 --> 12:57.778
I have already made up my mind.
I am doing this.

12:59.613 --> 13:00.948
I just wanna let you know.

13:18.465 --> 13:19.675
- Hi.
- Hi.

13:20.467 --> 13:22.886
You summoned me. Is this our sidebar?

13:22.886 --> 13:25.973
Yes, it is. Come on in. Have a seat.

13:26.557 --> 13:27.641
What can I do for you?

13:28.559 --> 13:31.645
Well, I have a request.

13:32.145 --> 13:33.814
You wanna meet my favorite oligarch?

13:35.357 --> 13:38.485
No. Well, I would--
I'd like to interview you.

13:39.152 --> 13:40.571
I'd love you on my show.

13:41.822 --> 13:43.991
I know. I know you don't do interviews.
I know.

13:43.991 --> 13:47.160
- But people are skeptical.
- Yeah, so you say.

13:47.160 --> 13:51.039
And I think it's a legitimate concern
for the shareholders.

13:51.039 --> 13:55.961
And this would be a beautiful opportunity
for you to tuck them in and show them

13:55.961 --> 13:58.297
- why they should support this deal.
- Yes.

13:58.297 --> 14:01.133
I also think it would be
a great opportunity for you.

14:01.133 --> 14:05.220
I said yes. Happy to do that.

14:06.263 --> 14:07.639
- Yes.
- So...

14:09.558 --> 14:11.101
No questions in advance.
That kind of thing?

14:11.101 --> 14:12.686
That's how your show works, right?

14:14.980 --> 14:16.106
Yes.

14:16.106 --> 14:19.234
And I assume
you don't have a problem with that.

14:19.234 --> 14:20.861
Okay. How's Thursday?

14:22.070 --> 14:23.530
Thursday. This Thur--

14:23.530 --> 14:25.365
- This Thursday, Thursday?
- Yeah.

14:25.365 --> 14:29.077
I have to be in Texas next week.
So, sorry.

14:29.077 --> 14:34.499
No. Yes, Thursday. That's great.
Thursday it is. Perfect.

14:34.499 --> 14:35.667
Where?

14:37.836 --> 14:39.755
Do you have a residence in this time zone?

14:41.089 --> 14:42.758
We can certainly use my place
in the Hamptons.

14:42.758 --> 14:45.093
- I can have Amanda set that up.
- Great.

14:46.345 --> 14:47.888
Did you think I was gonna say no?

14:48.680 --> 14:50.557
Yes. Kinda. I d--

14:51.475 --> 14:53.936
Well, I think you're right.

14:53.936 --> 14:55.812
I don't want there to be
any misunderstandings

14:55.812 --> 14:57.814
about what's going on here...

14:58.857 --> 15:00.859
- Yeah.
- ...with the deal.

15:00.859 --> 15:02.945
Yeah, exactly. Exactly.

15:04.613 --> 15:07.324
Right. So there. That's it. Great.

15:07.324 --> 15:11.745
I mean, Thursday it is,
in the Hamptons. So nice. All right.

15:11.745 --> 15:14.039
- I'm really looking forward to it.
- Me too.

15:14.039 --> 15:15.457
Great. Okay.

15:16.834 --> 15:19.419
- You know, this is your dressing room.
- Oh, fuck.

15:20.295 --> 15:21.755
Shouldn't I be the one to go?

15:24.758 --> 15:26.927
I say we splurge. It's our anniversary.

15:26.927 --> 15:28.387
What? It's not until June.

15:28.387 --> 15:31.223
No, it's not. It is April 30th.
Don't you remember?

15:31.974 --> 15:34.685
When we secretly held hands in the park
while we were covering the mobile morgue?

15:34.685 --> 15:37.062
- So romantic.
- That's when you're counting from?

15:37.062 --> 15:40.190
- Well, when do you count it?
- Our first kiss. Like a normal person.

15:40.190 --> 15:42.359
Come on. Niagara honeymoon package.

15:42.985 --> 15:45.779
Bottle of champagne. Cascading waterfall.

15:46.280 --> 15:47.948
Honeymoon package?

15:48.615 --> 15:50.659
I mean,
that's just what they call it, but...

15:52.244 --> 15:53.078
Okay.

15:54.121 --> 15:55.330
- Okay?
- Okay.

15:56.331 --> 15:58.542
Hey, so-- Very subtle.

15:58.542 --> 16:00.752
I need background on Paul Marks.
I'm interviewing him.

16:00.752 --> 16:03.005
Wait, what?
I thought that guy had a camera allergy.

16:03.005 --> 16:04.423
Well, he just got over it.

16:04.923 --> 16:06.717
Okay. And Cory signed off on this?

16:06.717 --> 16:09.469
I don't need Cory's permission
to interview him, all right?

16:09.469 --> 16:11.054
I want the world to know
we're an open book

16:11.054 --> 16:12.139
and we have nothing to hide.

16:12.139 --> 16:15.601
Okay? It's happening.
It's happening. And in two days.

16:15.601 --> 16:16.935
- What?
- What?

16:16.935 --> 16:18.187
- What?
- No.

16:19.313 --> 16:21.231
No. You see,
I can't prep an interview in two days,

16:21.231 --> 16:22.399
especially for someone like him.

16:22.399 --> 16:23.817
That's not possible.

16:23.817 --> 16:26.236
Well, you're just gonna have to
put your social life on hold.

16:27.613 --> 16:30.073
Wait a second.
You are each other's social life.

16:30.073 --> 16:31.158
This will be fun.

16:31.158 --> 16:33.243
You're just gonna get to cuddle,
read press clippings.

16:33.243 --> 16:35.370
- You love that joke so much. Yeah.
- I do.

16:35.370 --> 16:37.706
Listen, I have
the whole research department on it.

16:37.706 --> 16:40.042
It's gonna happen, and we can do it.
You can do it.

16:43.128 --> 16:44.671
All right, fuck it. Let's do it.

16:44.671 --> 16:45.881
Okay. You put out feelers,

16:45.881 --> 16:48.634
find out anyone who's related to him
or has slept with him. God willing, both.

16:48.634 --> 16:50.427
- Maybe somebody goes on the record.
- Yep. I'll get into it.

16:50.427 --> 16:51.512
Okay. Great.

16:51.512 --> 16:54.848
You know, he has bought or built dozens
of companies in the past 20 years.

16:54.848 --> 16:57.559
There's gotta be somebody who knows
something, right? Or hates his guts.

16:57.559 --> 17:02.105
Okay. Okay, here we go.
We're gonna do this.

17:04.900 --> 17:05.733
You got a sec?

17:05.733 --> 17:07.236
- Yeah. Come in.
- Great.

17:08.945 --> 17:09.946
You...

17:10.821 --> 17:13.407
crossed paths
with Paul Marks in Silicon Valley, right?

17:14.242 --> 17:15.743
Briefly. Why?

17:16.494 --> 17:17.621
What was he like back then?

17:18.413 --> 17:20.749
I don't know. Same as now.

17:20.749 --> 17:23.460
- Charming. Tall.
- Right.

17:25.503 --> 17:27.839
You ever, like, hear any shit
about him or anything?

17:29.091 --> 17:30.592
What do you mean exactly?

17:30.592 --> 17:33.887
You know, "shit."
