17:33.887 --> 17:35.639
blood transfusions from a 12-year-old boy.

17:35.639 --> 17:37.057
That kind of thing, you know.

17:37.558 --> 17:41.478
Honestly, I barely knew him.
I was still in school.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.064
So...

17:45.440 --> 17:48.151
Right, okay. I just figured-- Maybe.

17:50.571 --> 17:51.572
Why do you wanna know?

17:52.072 --> 17:57.202
Well, he and Alex are going to sit down
and talk on the record.

17:58.912 --> 18:02.374
So, obviously, if you think of anything...

18:03.083 --> 18:04.084
Yeah, yeah. Sure.

18:04.084 --> 18:05.377
Okay. Thanks.

18:17.306 --> 18:18.891
I wanna hit all five boroughs.

18:18.891 --> 18:23.103
And there's a ferry to Staten Island
that takes you right past Lady Liberty.

18:23.103 --> 18:25.480
- How much is that?
- It's actually free.

18:25.981 --> 18:27.274
Really? It's free?

18:27.274 --> 18:29.318
Definitely adding that to the list.

18:29.318 --> 18:32.696
And don't forget, babe, we have to hit
FAO Schwarz for the munchkin.

18:33.405 --> 18:35.157
What do you guys think
about swinging by UBA?

18:36.283 --> 18:37.284
Wow. Could we?

18:37.284 --> 18:39.453
Yeah,
I'll give you the whole VIP experience.

18:39.453 --> 18:42.289
You can watch me pre-tape a segment
for the <i>Evening News</i>.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.791
Yes, please. Yes.

18:44.791 --> 18:46.502
It's my pleasure. It'll be fun.

18:46.502 --> 18:51.215
Thank you. This is so exciting.
I can't wait to tell everyone back home.

18:51.215 --> 18:53.759
Hal, this is great.
I don't know what to wear.

19:02.309 --> 19:04.228
I think you look incredible
sitting up there.

19:04.228 --> 19:05.812
- Thank you.
- Don't you think, babe?

19:05.812 --> 19:08.232
- Yeah.
- Yes, I know you've been here before.

19:08.232 --> 19:10.692
Yeah, it was a while ago.

19:10.692 --> 19:12.986
Hal, good to see you again.
And you must be Cheryl.

19:12.986 --> 19:15.864
Yes.
Thank you so much for the VIP treatment.

19:15.864 --> 19:18.992
Well, it's not as flashy as
<i>The Morning Show</i>, but we do all right.

19:18.992 --> 19:20.994
Bradley,
this guy's having some tech issues,

19:20.994 --> 19:22.162
so the signal might drop.

19:22.162 --> 19:24.248
Yeah, no worries.
Thank you for organizing it.

19:24.248 --> 19:25.832
I know it was a bit of a scramble.

19:25.832 --> 19:29.670
I still think we should hold this one
until the hearings start in June.

19:29.670 --> 19:31.046
We can discuss later.

19:31.046 --> 19:32.881
Is this gonna be on the news tonight?

19:35.509 --> 19:36.552
It will indeed.

19:37.302 --> 19:39.555
- Do you guys wanna step back here?
- All right.

19:40.472 --> 19:42.808
- We're good to go?
- Counting you in now.

19:42.808 --> 19:46.520
- Thank you.
- In five, four, three...

19:48.897 --> 19:51.483
Ryder Flynt,
thank you so much for joining us.

19:52.401 --> 19:54.361
You are currently awaiting trial

19:54.361 --> 19:58.073
for assaulting a Capitol police officer
on January 6th.

19:58.073 --> 19:59.199
Is that correct?

19:59.199 --> 20:01.702
<i>I didn't think he
or anyone else had the right</i>

20:01.702 --> 20:03.203
<i>to keep us out of the Capitol.</i>

20:03.704 --> 20:06.498
<i>It's the people's house.
The people were screwed.</i>

20:06.498 --> 20:08.458
<i>So, the people, they needed to respond.</i>

20:08.458 --> 20:11.920
Did you believe
the 2020 election had been stolen?

20:12.963 --> 20:14.047
<i>Hundred percent.</i>

20:15.007 --> 20:19.011
And after everything you've learned since,
do you still believe that?

20:22.264 --> 20:23.724
<i>No. No.</i>

20:25.726 --> 20:29.938
If you had known then that the
former president's claims were baseless--

20:29.938 --> 20:31.607
<i>I would've stayed the hell home.</i>

20:34.443 --> 20:35.527
<i>I--</i>

20:38.197 --> 20:39.364
<i>I lost my job.</i>

20:42.201 --> 20:45.370
<i>My family, they won't talk to me.</i>

20:47.956 --> 20:50.334
I wanna just pause right there. I--

20:50.834 --> 20:54.546
The loss of your family,
do you feel like it was worth it?

20:55.380 --> 20:56.632
<i>What the hell do you think?</i>

20:58.175 --> 21:02.679
I think we don't pay enough attention
to the collateral damage of all of this.

21:07.017 --> 21:08.060
Take your time.

21:15.484 --> 21:17.653
So, I was thinking
that <i>TMS</i> could cross-promote

21:17.653 --> 21:19.029
- Alex's interview with Paul.
- Yes.

21:19.029 --> 21:21.240
Drive up our numbers, help UBA+.

21:21.240 --> 21:23.825
I love it. I'll get a shit ton of B-roll
while we're at the house.

21:23.825 --> 21:25.702
Great. So, if you get us footage
from that interview,

21:25.702 --> 21:27.496
we can cut together a sneak peek.

21:27.496 --> 21:29.456
Capitalize on all the noise out there
about the deal.

21:29.456 --> 21:30.541
Perfect. Yep.

21:30.541 --> 21:31.750
Stella, what do you think?

21:31.750 --> 21:34.545
It's your show. Just do what you want.

21:38.549 --> 21:41.635
I'm just saying,
we have to walk a fine line.

21:41.635 --> 21:44.263
It can't look like an ad,
like we're rolling over for him.

21:44.263 --> 21:46.056
Come on. You know that's not Alex's brand.

21:46.056 --> 21:49.852
How's prep?
Did you find anything interesting?

21:51.061 --> 21:53.313
No. There's not a lot of lead time
on this one.

21:53.313 --> 21:55.816
So, nothing?

21:55.816 --> 21:58.694
Let's just say I'd have a better chance
of digging up Jimmy Hoffa

21:58.694 --> 22:00.112
than finding this guy's yearbook photo.

22:00.112 --> 22:03.824
Yeah, but does it matter? I mean,
we want this to be a victory lap, right?

22:07.619 --> 22:09.663
- Well, I think we're good here.
- Yeah. We are.

22:09.663 --> 22:11.206
Okay. All right.

22:14.251 --> 22:16.003
So, were you guys...

22:38.650 --> 22:40.068
Hey, Chip.

22:45.365 --> 22:46.700
- Yeah. Okay.
- Yeah.

22:52.623 --> 22:54.291
Is there something you wanted to...

22:57.753 --> 22:58.837
We need to talk.

23:09.556 --> 23:11.266
Take your family to work day?

23:11.266 --> 23:13.310
Hal's wife wanted to see the studio.

23:14.102 --> 23:17.022
Interesting choice
to do that interview today.

23:18.106 --> 23:19.691
It had been booked for weeks.

23:20.859 --> 23:21.902
Bradley...

23:24.071 --> 23:25.572
do we have a problem?

23:26.907 --> 23:27.741
No.

23:28.951 --> 23:30.077
Because in my experience,

23:30.077 --> 23:34.206
Hal doesn't show up unless things are
about to get fucked six ways to Sunday.

23:34.206 --> 23:35.958
Look, I am handling it.

23:35.958 --> 23:37.167
Like you did last time?

23:39.169 --> 23:40.879
Just stop interfering, Cory.

23:41.463 --> 23:43.966
I know you think you're helping,
but you're just making it worse.

23:52.766 --> 23:56.645
Fix it, or I will.

24:27.926 --> 24:29.553
- Hey.
- Hi.

24:29.553 --> 24:30.971
I'm sorry I'm late.

24:33.140 --> 24:34.141
I missed you too.

24:34.641 --> 24:37.311
- I need a drink. Can we get a drink? Yeah.
- Okay. Yeah.

24:37.311 --> 24:40.189
Did I tell you? I think Audra's pregnant.

24:41.523 --> 24:42.858
What? Really?

24:42.858 --> 24:45.944
Yeah. I walked past her dressing room,
and all the lights were off,

24:45.944 --> 24:48.030
and she was sitting
in front of the mirror...

24:48.030 --> 24:49.156
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

24:49.156 --> 24:50.282
...rubbing her belly.

24:50.908 --> 24:52.326
Well, maybe she was meditating.

24:53.785 --> 24:54.953
Audra meditating?

24:54.953 --> 24:57.623
She talked through
our 9/11 moment of silence.

24:59.166 --> 25:00.000
- So, how's it going
- Yeah.

25:00.000 --> 25:01.502
with all the craziness over there?

25:03.128 --> 25:04.713
What craziness?

25:04.713 --> 25:06.173
Paul Marks. What's he like?

25:08.258 --> 25:10.511
Yeah. I don't think the deal is done.

25:11.178 --> 25:13.180
And who knows if it'll go through.

25:13.722 --> 25:15.057
- Right.
- Yeah.

25:21.730 --> 25:22.773
What are we doing?

25:24.942 --> 25:25.776
What do you mean?

25:27.903 --> 25:29.154
We meet up at Cory's party.

25:30.405 --> 25:32.407
You invite me to dinner and then cancel.

25:32.407 --> 25:35.327
And then tonight, you call me at
the last minute. Suddenly we're back on.

25:35.953 --> 25:38.747
And I don't know where your head is,
but I know it's not here.

25:38.747 --> 25:40.165
Well, I really--

25:42.042 --> 25:43.126
I wanted to see you.

25:43.126 --> 25:45.879
Did you really?
Or did you just need a drink?

25:47.506 --> 25:50.551
Look, Hal's in town
with Cheryl and the kid and--

25:50.551 --> 25:52.344
Right. Hal.

25:52.344 --> 25:56.890
No, it's not like that.
I know you hate him.

25:56.890 --> 25:58.475
- I don't hate Hal.
- Yes, you do.

25:58.475 --> 26:00.978
Whatever. It's fine.
I don't wanna get into it.

26:02.104 --> 26:06.191
Would you just talk to me?
I feel like we're on a bad first date.

26:17.119 --> 26:20.789
I should probably go. I--
They're gonna be wondering where I am.

26:20.789 --> 26:24.168
Bradley, it's me.
You can tell me anything.

26:27.921 --> 26:31.717
I'm a mess, okay?
And I don't want to drag you down with me.

26:32.259 --> 26:33.260
I'm sorry.

26:34.636 --> 26:36.138
I think I should get the check.

26:37.890 --> 26:38.891
Yeah.

27:23.227 --> 27:24.228
Hey.

27:25.521 --> 27:28.440
I really, really loved
that Scared Straight interview.

27:28.440 --> 27:30.192
- Oh, yeah?
- I just wanna say, message received.

27:30.192 --> 27:31.276
- All right.
- Meant a lot to me.

27:31.276 --> 27:32.778
- You don't want to get locked up, Hal.
- No, yeah.

27:32.778 --> 27:34.238
You think you're tough, but you're not.

27:34.238 --> 27:40.661
Listen to me. I need to do this
for my family, for my sobriety.

27:40.661 --> 27:41.912
- For your sobriety?
- Yes!

27:41.912 --> 27:46.750
Oh, my God. Please do not weaponize your
addiction to prove some fucking point.

27:46.750 --> 27:48.126
I mean, that is just a dick move.

27:48.126 --> 27:50.921
Have you even thought
about what this is going to do to me?

27:50.921 --> 27:52.005
Oh, my God. You're right.

27:52.005 --> 27:54.007
I haven't thought about
what's gonna happen to you,

27:54.007 --> 27:57.344
except for the fact that, like, you could
have deleted that footage, right?

27:57.344 --> 27:59.137
- All of it. You could have deleted it.
- That's a--

27:59.137 --> 28:01.598
That's what I thought that you would do
when I left DC.

28:02.099 --> 28:06.395
And then I saw it on TV, and I thought,
"Why the fuck would she use this?"

28:06.395 --> 28:07.479
And then I reali-- No.

28:07.479 --> 28:10.357
Because then I realized that
you will do anything to get ahead.

28:10.357 --> 28:11.608
- Me?
- Yes.

28:12.109 --> 28:14.194
You are gonna ruin our lives.
You know that, right?

28:14.194 --> 28:16.154
Well, you know what?
I learned from the best, right?

28:16.154 --> 28:18.782
You turned in Dad.
That kind of fucked us all up, right?

28:19.449 --> 28:20.576
- Wow.
- Except for you.

28:20.576 --> 28:21.910
You've come out on top, haven't you?

28:21.910 --> 28:24.997
Are you kidding me? Like,
you think this was some sort of long game

28:24.997 --> 28:27.499
I was playing to get to New York City
and somehow end up on the n--

28:27.499 --> 28:29.418
What the fuck are you even talking about?

28:31.170 --> 28:34.506
I know what it is like
to look at my father and have no respect.

28:35.424 --> 28:36.425
None.

28:37.676 --> 28:39.845
I don't want my daughter
to look at me like that.

28:41.346 --> 28:42.431
That would fucking kill me.

28:42.431 --> 28:44.433
You think your daughter's
gonna respect her dad

28:44.433 --> 28:46.351
who's locked up just like our fucking dad?

28:47.019 --> 28:50.272
You're gonna ruin her life. You're gonna
ruin Cheryl's life and ruin my life.

28:50.272 --> 28:51.690
You know what? You're drunk.

28:51.690 --> 28:54.526
I think that you should have some water
before you go to bed.

28:54.526 --> 28:57.279
You're Jesus Christ
on the goddamn cross. Really?

29:14.087 --> 29:15.088
Hey.

29:15.672 --> 29:17.591
- Hey, you.
- Hey.

29:17.591 --> 29:18.926
You're here early.

29:18.926 --> 29:22.679
Yeah, I just had some stuff
I had to clean off my desk.

29:24.765 --> 29:25.807
What's going on? You okay?

29:26.558 --> 29:31.855
Yeah, I'm--
You know, I really appreciate you

29:32.523 --> 29:36.235
just always supporting me
and having my back since I've been here.

29:36.235 --> 29:38.195
It just-- It means a lot.

29:38.695 --> 29:40.697
Okay, well, that sounds like a goodbye.

29:41.490 --> 29:43.367
Is NBN trying to poach you?

29:43.951 --> 29:47.829
No, I just forget to say it sometimes,
and I know what you've done.

29:48.413 --> 29:50.832
Yeah. And you didn't have to do
all that, you know?

29:50.832 --> 29:52.209
I know. Okay.

29:52.918 --> 29:55.170
- Oh, God. Honey, I have to go.
- Yeah.

29:55.170 --> 29:57.548
I'm interviewing Paul Marks later today.

29:58.382 --> 29:59.967
I know it's just been--

30:01.426 --> 30:02.427
What?

30:02.427 --> 30:06.014
Chip found out some information on him,

30:06.014 --> 30:08.141
and I know I'm gonna have to
go at him really hard.

30:08.141 --> 30:09.643
- Really?
- Yeah.

30:09.643 --> 30:11.979
- Well...
- It's just not good.

30:11.979 --> 30:13.522
The deal could possibly blow up,

30:14.273 --> 30:16.900
and I hate the idea of
doing that to people.

30:16.900 --> 30:19.027
But if there really is something,

30:19.945 --> 30:21.530
- isn't it better to know now...
- Yes.

30:21.530 --> 30:23.282
- ...than too late?
- I know. I know.

30:23.949 --> 30:26.994
It's what we do.
We hold people to account, right?

30:28.203 --> 30:30.247
That's right. That's what we do.

30:30.247 --> 30:31.331
That's what we do.

30:31.331 --> 30:34.001
- Yeah.
- Okay. I'm around.

30:34.543 --> 30:35.711
- Yeah. Okay.
- Okay.

30:35.711 --> 30:37.171
- Have a good interview.
- Thanks, honey.

30:59.234 --> 31:00.903
God, that was a long drive.

31:00.903 --> 31:02.821
- Yep.
- Okay, let's do this.

31:04.698 --> 31:05.699
Should we just go in?

31:05.699 --> 31:07.367
- I mean, yeah.
- Yeah. Let's do it.

31:09.828 --> 31:10.829
Hello?

31:13.457 --> 31:14.291
Hello?

31:17.961 --> 31:19.213
Hello!

31:20.047 --> 31:21.298
Oh, my gosh.

31:21.298 --> 31:22.508
Sorry. He's friendly.

31:22.508 --> 31:24.134
- Hi, there.
- Good. You found it.

31:24.134 --> 31:25.469
You're not dressed.

31:25.469 --> 31:28.055
- The turn-on can be a little tricky.
- Excuse me?

31:28.055 --> 31:29.640
Turning onto the road. It's unmarked.

31:29.640 --> 31:32.851
Oh, right. No, we actually-- We got it.

31:32.851 --> 31:37.898
So, this is quite a beautiful hidden gem
you have here. Wow.

31:38.398 --> 31:41.276
Listen, I know it's probably gonna
take you guys a couple minutes

31:41.276 --> 31:42.861
to get set up and whatnot.

31:43.487 --> 31:45.739
Help yourself to whatever you want,
and I will go get ready.

31:45.739 --> 31:47.366
Let's go. Buddy, come on. Let's go.

31:49.952 --> 31:52.079
Okay, okay. Hi.

31:54.915 --> 31:57.000
No, no. That's fine. Thanks.

32:01.463 --> 32:02.506
Good?

32:04.383 --> 32:05.926
Okay.

32:08.220 --> 32:11.598
So-- Sorry. What are the rules?

32:11.598 --> 32:12.683
What do you mean?

32:13.183 --> 32:15.227
Well, do I know you? Do I not know you?

32:15.227 --> 32:20.065
Oh, yeah. Just think of it like, you know,
we're just meeting for the first time.

32:21.483 --> 32:22.693
Easy.

32:22.693 --> 32:24.945
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

32:25.612 --> 32:26.613
All right.

32:27.781 --> 32:28.782
Chip.

32:29.825 --> 32:30.826
Okay.

32:30.826 --> 32:32.661
- All right. Everybody ready?
- Yes.

32:32.661 --> 32:33.745
- All set.
- Let's do this.

32:33.745 --> 32:35.247
Let's roll cameras, please.

32:35.247 --> 32:37.207
So, why don't you do interviews?

32:38.166 --> 32:40.878
- Well, I don't want to offend you.
- Oh, please, offend me.

32:40.878 --> 32:43.630
I think they're a waste of time, honestly.

32:43.630 --> 32:45.132
I think people come in with an agenda

32:45.132 --> 32:47.050
and wait for the other person
to prove them right.

32:47.050 --> 32:49.052
And I would
literally rather do anything else.

32:49.052 --> 32:50.804
I would rather go hunting
with Dick Cheney.

32:50.804 --> 32:52.598
I would rather stand in line at the DMV.

32:52.598 --> 32:55.309
Well, then why did you agree
to sit down with me?

32:55.976 --> 33:02.107
Because I think this deal is important,
and you asked me.

33:05.027 --> 33:07.154
Well, when someone with your resources

33:07.154 --> 33:09.448
acquires a company like UBA,

33:09.448 --> 33:10.949
it raises a lot of questions.

33:11.867 --> 33:15.704
So, why do you wanna add
a media empire to your portfolio?

33:16.205 --> 33:17.623
Well, I don't have one.

33:18.248 --> 33:19.458
So we're your trophy?

33:19.458 --> 33:23.337
No. I think there's tremendous
profit potential at UBA,

33:23.337 --> 33:24.588
and I hate fake news.

33:25.422 --> 33:27.591
Says the guy from big tech.

33:27.591 --> 33:30.719
Right. Okay. Sure. I get it.

33:30.719 --> 33:33.222
I think we can all agree at this point
it's probably healthier

33:33.222 --> 33:36.558
to smoke a pack of cigarettes
than it is to log on to Twitter, right?

33:36.558 --> 33:38.477
But good luck
keeping people from scrolling.

33:41.146 --> 33:42.731
I think the news can be fixed.

33:43.815 --> 33:47.319
And I'd like to give it a try
before it's too late.

33:47.319 --> 33:49.571
And you think you can fix the news?

33:49.571 --> 33:52.366
I don't see anybody else
with their hand raised.

33:52.366 --> 33:54.993
And what makes you think
you're qualified for the job?

33:54.993 --> 33:57.329
Well, the bar does seem
to be set pretty low.

33:59.790 --> 34:03.001
Sounds like you don't have a lot
of respect for people that do the news.

34:04.002 --> 34:05.671
Should we be concerned about that,

34:05.671 --> 34:08.215
partnering with someone
that doesn't respect us?

34:08.215 --> 34:10.342
I could ask you the very same question.

34:11.342 --> 34:15.264
You thought I was so bad for UBA
that you ditched the <i>Hyperion One</i> launch.

34:15.264 --> 34:16.598
Should I be concerned about you?

34:17.516 --> 34:20.686
I mean, that is what happened, right?
And this is <i>Alex Unfiltered</i>.

34:20.686 --> 34:24.857
Well, that might be what happened,
but it had nothing to do with respect.

34:24.857 --> 34:28.610
There were, and there are still,
concerns about you buying this company

34:28.610 --> 34:30.612
and I believe that the jury is still out.

34:30.612 --> 34:33.699
I certainly hear that.
That-- You've made that very, very clear.

34:33.699 --> 34:35.909
Is that why you were hanging out
outside my hotel?

34:42.833 --> 34:47.629
You know what?
Why don't we just take a quick break?

34:48.213 --> 34:49.715
- Okay. Sure.
- That okay?

34:50.299 --> 34:51.382
- Be right back.
- Okay.

34:56.263 --> 34:57.097
Are you doing okay?

34:57.097 --> 34:58.098
Yeah.

34:58.098 --> 35:01.768
Okay. Are you gonna ask him
about the Stanford student?

35:04.313 --> 35:05.689
Hey, nail his ass.

35:06.732 --> 35:09.610
I know. I'm on it.

35:09.610 --> 35:10.736
Okay.

35:28.795 --> 35:33.800
You ran an incubator in Palo Alto,
mentoring young innovators in tech.

35:34.384 --> 35:36.845
I did.
I started it during the dot-com boom.

35:36.845 --> 35:38.680
A lot of great ideas
came out of that project.

35:39.515 --> 35:40.807
But then you stepped away.

35:41.308 --> 35:45.604
Yes. Our aerospace division
started gaining traction.

35:45.604 --> 35:47.981
I was spending a lot more time in Texas,
so I handed it off.

35:50.108 --> 35:51.109
Any regrets?

35:53.070 --> 35:54.905
Not sure what you mean.

35:54.905 --> 35:58.492
Well, a former Stanford student
who was in that incubator

35:58.492 --> 36:00.160
claims to have written a code.

36:00.869 --> 36:03.997
A code that evolved
into the data analytics system

36:03.997 --> 36:06.333
that you sell to governments
around the world.

36:07.376 --> 36:09.419
Right. Well, that software
took years to develop

36:09.419 --> 36:13.048
and went through hundreds of iterations
before it became what it is today.

36:14.049 --> 36:17.052
Yes. But the initial idea was theirs.

36:17.052 --> 36:20.472
Well, the initial idea was,
if I recall correctly,

36:20.472 --> 36:23.600
a GPS blocker for activists
and dissidents,

36:23.600 --> 36:27.729
which we took to several VCs,
all of whom passed.

36:28.313 --> 36:30.148
So then you bought it instead.

36:31.358 --> 36:35.070
A billion-dollar idea
at a bargain price of 50 grand.

36:35.070 --> 36:38.407
- Is that what you paid? Fifty grand?
- I bought quite a few ideas

36:38.407 --> 36:39.575
out of that incubator.

36:40.158 --> 36:43.036
All of those deals were,
at the time, industry standard.

36:44.496 --> 36:46.331
Well, it also used to be industry standard

36:46.331 --> 36:49.668
that a director would fuck an actress
on a casting couch, so...

36:50.169 --> 36:53.672
Or a news anchor might have a button
underneath his desk to lock the door.

36:55.048 --> 36:57.593
Are you rich
because you stole someone else's idea?

36:58.302 --> 37:00.262
I never forced anybody
to sign any contracts.

37:00.262 --> 37:02.181
That person sold their idea on their own.

37:02.181 --> 37:06.810
But you did make them sign an NDA
and then took a progressive idea

37:06.810 --> 37:09.730
and converted it
into a predictive policing tool.

37:11.315 --> 37:14.151
Well, I mean, we both understand
the concept of an NDA.

37:14.735 --> 37:17.696
One person wins
and the other person is silenced.

37:18.447 --> 37:22.784
So, is it fair to use them
against young college students

37:22.784 --> 37:25.120
when they might not be experienced enough

37:25.120 --> 37:28.874
to understand the implications
of what they're signing?

37:28.874 --> 37:31.877
Now, everybody involved in
this transaction was an adult.

37:31.877 --> 37:34.171
Well, this student did not feel
very good about it.

37:34.755 --> 37:37.341
And, in fact,
suffered debilitating depression

37:38.091 --> 37:39.593
as well as a suicide attempt.

37:46.016 --> 37:49.895
Well, I'm sorry. I had no idea.

37:53.065 --> 37:55.651
Well, do you have any response?

37:57.402 --> 37:59.196
To this former student?

37:59.196 --> 38:00.906
To the people watching the interview?

38:04.034 --> 38:05.827
Well, I think that...

38:18.465 --> 38:22.302
You know, I used to sleep
on the floor of my factory,

38:22.970 --> 38:25.848
sometimes for weeks at a time.

38:25.848 --> 38:30.686
When we were developing
the first prototype for <i>Hyperion One</i>,

38:30.686 --> 38:34.815
my engineers and I would work 18,
20-some-odd hours every day.

38:37.818 --> 38:42.447
When I focus on something,
I tend to block out everything else.

38:46.702 --> 38:50.122
So when I finally went home,
my wife had left.

38:51.456 --> 38:57.754
She had taken everything that was hers,
and the house was a blank.

39:00.632 --> 39:03.260
I don't even know how long
she'd been gone. Could have been weeks.

39:06.513 --> 39:09.183
I had to take
a pretty hard look at myself.

39:11.560 --> 39:16.315
The way I treated other people.
The cost... of what I was doing.

39:20.819 --> 39:23.614
And I have since changed
my company's policies

39:23.614 --> 39:26.575
as well as my own personal behavior
and beliefs.

39:27.242 --> 39:32.706
So I think I probably owe that student,
at the very least,

39:34.583 --> 39:35.584
a conversation.

39:49.139 --> 39:50.140
Next question.

40:06.698 --> 40:10.661
While the President says he'll work
towards a solution to the current impasse,

40:10.661 --> 40:14.456
congressional leaders continue
to push back on several key points.

40:14.456 --> 40:16.875
And when we come back...

40:22.172 --> 40:23.173
When we come back...

40:26.760 --> 40:27.719
Bradley, what's up?

40:30.597 --> 40:31.974
<i>Bradley!</i>

40:32.683 --> 40:35.853
When we come back,
we'll take a closer look at homeschooling.

40:36.937 --> 40:39.189
We'll meet one mother who,
during the pandemic,

40:39.189 --> 40:43.360
decided her kids would never return
to their traditional classroom again.

40:45.863 --> 40:46.864
And we're out.

40:54.037 --> 40:54.872
Hi.

40:58.333 --> 41:01.503
- Brad's not here. She's--
- I know. I came to talk to you.

41:02.254 --> 41:03.255
Can I come in?

41:09.386 --> 41:13.098
I made a lot of assumptions about you
before even meeting you.

41:15.309 --> 41:16.560
That sounds about right.

41:17.477 --> 41:18.562
I think--

41:19.271 --> 41:23.525
I think I made Bradley choose between us
when your mom was sick.

41:24.902 --> 41:27.821
I think that's how Bradley felt,
and that wasn't fair.

41:28.822 --> 41:32.159
And I may have encouraged her...

41:34.244 --> 41:35.662
to cut you out of her life.

41:36.496 --> 41:38.332
So you could have her all for yourself?

41:44.296 --> 41:45.756
I'm sorry.

41:47.090 --> 41:49.092
What I mean is that...

41:52.846 --> 41:56.058
I think Bradley wants to be with me,
and I want that too.

41:57.059 --> 41:58.727
But we had dinner the other night,

41:58.727 --> 42:02.523
and she seemed really anxious
about starting things up again.

42:03.023 --> 42:06.527
And I think that had a lot to do with you.

42:07.361 --> 42:09.321
I mean, how I judged you.

42:09.321 --> 42:11.823
She doesn't talk to me
about those kinds of things.

42:11.823 --> 42:13.825
- I don't--
- Well, I think she's scared to.

42:14.660 --> 42:16.870
- Because whenever she brings you in--
- I fuck it up.

42:16.870 --> 42:18.830
- No. No.
- Yeah.

42:19.790 --> 42:22.709
You see her in a way
that no one else does.

42:23.210 --> 42:24.545
She can't hide with you.

42:29.633 --> 42:34.555
If you could just support us, I think
it would mean a lot to Bradley and to me.

42:35.722 --> 42:41.228
If I just had a chance,
I know I could make her happy.

42:51.238 --> 42:52.990
I'll think on it.

42:55.367 --> 42:56.577
I'll think on it, okay?

43:02.291 --> 43:03.500
Well, that was fun.

43:04.835 --> 43:05.919
When's it gonna air?

43:05.919 --> 43:07.963
Next week. We're actually
gonna be editing this weekend.

43:07.963 --> 43:11.258
So, Alex, you heading back to the city?

43:11.967 --> 43:14.136
Yeah, in a minute. Thanks, Chip.

43:14.136 --> 43:16.221
Okay. I'm having some ideas
on the shape of the show,

43:16.221 --> 43:19.099
so if you wanna talk while you drive,
cut the trailer tonight.

43:19.099 --> 43:22.102
- You know how Mia's always hounding us--
- Yeah, good.

43:22.102 --> 43:23.854
Sure. I'll call you from the car.

43:27.065 --> 43:28.483
Chip, let's go.

43:29.818 --> 43:32.154
- Yeah.
- Okay. Yeah, sorry. Let me walk you out.

43:34.823 --> 43:35.908
Just be careful on the turn.

43:35.908 --> 43:37.326
- Thanks, Paul.
- You know it, guys.

43:37.326 --> 43:38.785
- Have a good one.
- Thank you.

43:41.872 --> 43:43.207
Well, you survived that.

43:43.790 --> 43:45.167
Well, you didn't pull any punches.

43:45.167 --> 43:46.877
Oh, well, that's the idea.

43:49.379 --> 43:50.214
I'm curious though.

43:50.214 --> 43:53.175
How did you find out about her?
This Stanford student.

43:53.717 --> 43:57.804
You know I can't tell you that.
And honestly, I don't know who it is.

43:58.889 --> 44:01.266
Well, it's fair game that you did that.

44:02.142 --> 44:03.477
I like that you went there.

44:04.770 --> 44:06.021
- You liked that?
- Yeah.

44:06.021 --> 44:09.983
Most people in your position wouldn't
come after me like that, but you did.

44:10.609 --> 44:11.610
Impressive.

44:12.194 --> 44:16.240
Well, UBA has certain standards,
and this deal doesn't change that.

44:18.242 --> 44:19.660
Even if it does happen,

44:20.244 --> 44:23.372
it's, you know--
it's not like we're in bed together.

44:24.748 --> 44:28.752
- I mean it metaphorically speaking.
- Right.

44:28.752 --> 44:29.670
You know?

44:30.170 --> 44:31.171
And literally.

44:31.964 --> 44:36.426
No. We're not in bed.

44:36.426 --> 44:37.886
We should keep it that way.

44:41.598 --> 44:43.433
We're in furious agreement.

44:43.934 --> 44:45.435
I've never been more furious.

44:59.658 --> 45:01.535
I don't think we should do this.

45:02.369 --> 45:03.662
Right. Never happened.

45:07.165 --> 45:10.919
I'm gonna go grab my--
I forgot my-- Forgot my coat over here.

45:10.919 --> 45:13.380
No, where's-- My coat's right in my--

45:13.380 --> 45:14.840
Did I forget anything else?

45:15.799 --> 45:18.218
Did you forget anything else?
I don't think you forgot anything.

45:18.218 --> 45:19.386
I don't think I did.

46:32.376 --> 46:34.086
Let's get married in Niagara.

46:35.629 --> 46:36.630
- What?
- Let's do it.

46:37.172 --> 46:39.883
Let's get a justice of the peace
and some witnesses

46:39.883 --> 46:42.761
and some weird outfits
and just fucking do it.

46:44.179 --> 46:45.639
Is that a yes or--

46:45.639 --> 46:46.723
No.

46:47.975 --> 46:49.059
No.

46:50.519 --> 46:51.728
- No.
- I'm sorry.

46:53.647 --> 46:56.900
I thought this was what you wanted.
So, what is...

47:00.821 --> 47:04.658
What? Hold-- What?
Did I totally fucking misread this?

47:05.284 --> 47:08.745
You are the one who's been dropping
clues for, like, three months now,

47:08.745 --> 47:10.914
and you talked about a ring.

47:10.914 --> 47:14.585
I mean, maybe I didn't,
you know, propose in the best way.

47:14.585 --> 47:16.503
We were planning a huge interview.

47:17.087 --> 47:18.088
But...

47:19.840 --> 47:21.550
Just tell me what you want.
That's what we'll do.

47:21.550 --> 47:23.302
I mean, tell me what you want. We can--

47:23.302 --> 47:25.012
I want you to ask because of me.

47:26.638 --> 47:27.639
Not because of her.

47:32.102 --> 47:34.396
That's ridiculous.

47:37.149 --> 47:38.275
Come on.

48:03.550 --> 48:04.551
Hal?

48:06.595 --> 48:07.596
Cheryl?

48:46.385 --> 48:48.929
Wow. That was a really nice way
to wake up.

48:54.017 --> 48:56.061
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

49:13.120 --> 49:15.038
- There you go.
- Oh, God.

49:15.747 --> 49:17.332
Okay.

49:21.795 --> 49:22.796
Cory.

49:22.796 --> 49:23.881
<i>Hey. Too early?</i>

49:23.881 --> 49:25.549
No. No, never.

49:25.549 --> 49:29.469
Listen, whatever interview stunt
Alex was up to, don't worry.

49:29.469 --> 49:31.889
We won't use it unless it works for us.

49:31.889 --> 49:35.976
Went well, actually.
I think it'll be good for perception.

49:35.976 --> 49:39.062
<i>Well, that's great to hear. Alex is--</i>

49:39.062 --> 49:41.106
She's passionate about her work.

49:41.106 --> 49:44.818
Well, she was phenomenal.

49:45.944 --> 49:47.362
Stunning, really.

49:48.322 --> 49:50.407
Kinda blew my mind,
if you wanna know the truth.

49:53.493 --> 49:54.620
Well...

49:56.580 --> 49:59.458
you can see
why she's such a key asset to the company.

49:59.458 --> 50:00.751
Sure do.

50:03.754 --> 50:06.882
Hey, listen. I know marketing
is pushing for a new logo,

50:06.882 --> 50:10.802
but I don't think Hyperion needs to be
so front-facing in the branding.

50:11.386 --> 50:15.557
Keep it simple, right?
The less friction, the better.

50:16.266 --> 50:18.810
<i>Good. On that, we are simpatico.</i>

50:20.020 --> 50:22.481
Okay. I will talk to you.

50:22.481 --> 50:23.565
<i>Perfect. I--</i>

50:26.193 --> 50:28.570
- Wow.
- Wow.

50:43.502 --> 50:45.254
Laura.

50:47.047 --> 50:49.049
- Hey.
- Hey.

50:56.306 --> 50:59.977
I'm sorry about dinner
the other night. I was awful.

51:02.646 --> 51:05.732
And-- It-- And it was fine.

51:06.233 --> 51:07.359
Hal is fine.

51:08.986 --> 51:09.987
It was nothing.

51:14.283 --> 51:18.245
I just miss you. I really miss you.

51:33.594 --> 51:37.806
<i>You know, I used to sleep on the floor
of my factory,</i>

51:38.432 --> 51:41.435
<i>sometimes for weeks at a time.</i>

51:41.435 --> 51:46.190
<i>When we were developing
the first prototype for</i> Hyperion One<i>,</i>

51:46.190 --> 51:50.569
<i>my engineers and I would work 18,
20-some-odd hours every day.</i>

51:50.569 --> 51:51.737
How does it play?

51:51.737 --> 51:55.908
<i>When I focus on something,
I tend to block out every--</i>

51:58.785 --> 51:59.912
You come off well.

52:01.914 --> 52:03.248
You could've talked to me.

52:05.334 --> 52:06.752
I had no idea you felt that way.

52:07.711 --> 52:09.713
I wasn't sure how I felt.

52:11.632 --> 52:12.674
How about now?

52:13.550 --> 52:16.428
I'll have my lawyers reach out.
I can leave quietly.

52:17.638 --> 52:20.599
I don't wanna make this transition
any more uncomfortable.

52:20.599 --> 52:22.351
So, you're gonna quit?

52:22.935 --> 52:24.478
Yeah. I think it's for the best.

52:24.478 --> 52:27.523
Stella, come on. UBA is stuck in the past.

52:28.106 --> 52:31.235
They need someone with a vision
to move this place forward.

52:32.778 --> 52:35.072
I think that person is you.

52:36.281 --> 52:38.867
- Cory might disagree.
- Cory won't be here.

52:43.330 --> 52:45.332
I'm sending you an offer of employment.

52:45.832 --> 52:50.420
As soon as the shareholders agree
to this merger, you will take Cory's job.

52:54.341 --> 52:56.009
That's a big leap.

52:56.510 --> 52:58.428
There's gonna be a lot of pushback.

52:58.428 --> 53:00.556
Well, what did we always say?
We don't play by the rules--

53:00.556 --> 53:01.765
We make them.

53:04.893 --> 53:06.270
What do you think, Stella?

53:08.313 --> 53:09.523
You wanna run this place?
